    "stdyInfo": {
      "abstract": [
        {
          "contentType": "purpose",
          "lang": "fr",
          "value": "Stratégies thérapeutiques : évaluation clinique à moyen et long terme Utilisation de méthodologies innovantes comme les méthodes de ‘comparative effectiveness’ Morbi-mortalité sévère SIDA et non SIDA et impact de l’infection à VIH et/ou des traitements Infections Cancers Infarctus du myocarde Fractures Santé Publique et infection à VIH en France Survie Présentation tardive Migrants Co-infection VHC Indicateurs de prises en charge (cascade)"
        },
        {
          "contentType": "purpose",
          "lang": "en",
          "value": "General objective: To evaluate the medium and long-term clinical impact of therapeutic strategies with the help of marginal structural models. Secondary objectives - to assess non-AIDS-defining morbidity and mortality and the impact of HIV infection and/or treatment for cancer as well as vascular and metabolic diseases. - to contribute to epidemiological monitoring of HIV infection in France (descriptive epidemiology and establishment of model). - to participate in international collaborations on treated patient prognosis as well as morbidity and mortality in previously diagnosed individuals."
        }
      ],
